      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is content creation automation?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Content creation automation uses AI and software to reduce or eliminate manual steps in producing content. The spectrum ranges from AI writing assistants that draft content faster to fully automated services that write, optimize, and publish without human input.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can automated content rank on Google?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Google evaluates content quality, not production method. Our 3,500+ published articles maintain a 92% average SEO score. The key is content that matches search intent and provides genuine value. The creation method is irrelevant.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the difference between AI writing tools and content automation?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">AI writing tools generate text — you still do keyword research, editing, formatting, and publishing. Content automation handles the full pipeline: research, writing, optimization, formatting, and publishing. Most tools on this list are AI writers. Only a few automate the entire workflow from keyword to published page.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do I still need writers if I use content automation tools?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">It depends on automation level. Semi-automated tools (Jasper, Copy.ai, Writesonic) still need human editing. Fully automated services (theStacc) do not. If you choose AI-assisted tools, you need editors. If you choose full autopilot, you don't.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much does content creation automation cost per article?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Ranges from $0.10/article (Byword at Enterprise scale) to $3.30/article (theStacc at $99 for 30 articles) to $150+/article (freelance writers). The per-article cost drops dramatically with automation. The trade-off is control — cheaper per article usually means less customization.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is fully automated content as good as human-written content?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">For informational SEO content, automated content performs comparably. For thought leadership, case studies, and opinion pieces, human writers still produce better output. Match the automation level to the content type — use automation for volume, humans for depth.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What CMS platforms work with content automation tools?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">WordPress has the most integrations — every tool on this list connects to it. Webflow and Ghost are supported by theStacc, Letterdrop, and Narrato. Custom CMS platforms work with theStacc (via webhook), Copy.ai (via API), and Zapier-connected workflows.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How many articles per month can content automation tools produce?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">From 25/month (Byword Starter) to 1,000/month (Byword Enterprise). theStacc produces 30–80/month depending on plan. AI writing tools like Jasper and Copy.ai have no article limit — but you still spend time editing each one. Unlimited drafts doesn't mean unlimited published articles.</div>
